American used vehicle exporting is a grey-market international trade involving the exporting of used cars from the United States to international markets.
The most exported cars from the United States include Ford Motor Company (Lincoln, Mercury), General Motors, and Fiat Chrysler Automobiles (formerly Chrysler) (Dodge, Ram Trucks (formerly Dodge Ram)), (Big Three), Mercedes-Benz, Toyota, Nissan, and other makes. Hummer is also a sight around the world.
Most exported American used cars can be seen in Europe (including Iceland), Asia (Japan, etc.), Oceania (Australia, New Zealand, etc.), Eurasia (Russia and Turkey) among other countries.
